%N A396153 a(n) is the number of possible outcomes having a run of 4 or more sixes when a die is rolled n times.
%H A396153 <a href="/index/Rec#order_05">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (11,-25,-25,-25,-30).
%F A396153 G.f.: x^4/((6*x - 1)*(5*x^4 + 5*x^3 + 5*x^2 + 5*x - 1)).
%F A396153 a(n) = A396158(n,4).
%F A396153 a(n) ~ 6^n. - _Stefano Spezia_, May 18 2026
%t A396153 LinearRecurrence[{11, -25, -25, -25, -30}, {0, 0, 0, 0, 1}, 26] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 18 2026 *)
%o A396153 (PARI) concat([0, 0, 0, 0], Vec(x^4/((6*x-1)*(5*x^4+5*x^3+5*x^2+5*x-1)) + O(x^26)))
